## Minimum prefix length: **8 hex chars** for all entities

Telemetry confirms **8-char UI truncation is the floor** — and 12-char is the most common real-world input. Accepting 8 chars covers all observed UI-copy cases. Multi-match branch handles inevitable 8-char collisions by showing candidates rather than auto-picking.

| Entity | ID length | Min fuzzy prefix | Collision handling |
|--------|-----------|-------------------|---------------------|
| event / trace / log | 32 | 8 | Scope to project + window; `multiple-matches` → candidate list |
| span | 16 | 8 | Scoped within `traceId`; effectively unique |

